Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a false equivalency. Providing a service or good to bolster economic growth is not the same as being forced to give your money to the government.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Lack of regulation](https://www.drugabuse.gov/drugs-abuse/opioids/opioid-overdose-crisis#three) has been a significant cause of the opioid crisis.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar compound will always exist.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Reducing the number of users and frequency of use is just a means to an end. The end goal is to reduce harms created by drug use. It's perfectly possible to increase use and have less overall harm. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legal shifts the focus of the police from investigating crimes where individuals damaged others instead of themselves. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The climb out of poverty is not helped by wasting resources on ingesting toxic materials.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is only true in the case of people whose drug use either causes them to become dangerous or interferes with their lives. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalisation of cigarettes [did not stop](https://thedebrief.co.uk/news/real-life/1-every-7-british-cigarettes-contraband-counterfeit/) illicit and poor quality cheaper versions. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While neither seems acceptable, most would rather face prejudice than prison. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This limits what we know about these compounds as well as to what length we are able to develop treatments for those struggling with addiction \\(physical and mental\\) as well as treatment for acute toxicity.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs have recreational and social value.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates negatively with socially-responsible behavior. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Cheap [substitutes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Desomorphine#Toxicity_of_%22krokodil%22) like krokodil cause severe health problems. If drugs were legal and cheaper, substitutes lose popularity.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Creativity can be stimulated through the use of drugs. Drugs could help us to live in a more creative dynamic society.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Giving a legal framework to the use of certain drugs may help to prevent the development of infectious diseases.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising strong opioids such as heroin would only exacerbate the opioid crisis.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Much of this revenue may be attributed to people who became addicted before they were aware of the negative health consequences. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The Federal Government \\(US\\) has no constitutional authority to regulate what citizens choose to put in their bodies. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The only way to know if the related compound acts the same is by doing the research that was banned in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising all drugs may give private companies incentives to advertise/promote the use of those, potentially leading to an increase the overall drug use.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use has a negative effect on freedom and, therefore, ought to be contained.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is [no/little research](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/drugfacts/hallucinogens) regarding the long-term effects of hallucinogens. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-cocaine laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the early 1900s were directed at black men in the South.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If this was true, cartels would already be moving over to newer, patented pharmaceuticals, whose costs of production is dwarfed by market price already.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Education including factual data will promote responsible and thoughtful use of drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will remove the taboo that drug addiction currently carries with it. As a result, addicts will no longer be a target of prejudice. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The fact that legalising drugs would not "end all crime" does not means that it would not damage criminal organizations. It\'s a step in the right direction to reduce their power.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs means that they are taken, and disposed of, more safely and cautiously than in the current environment.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Ending the war on drugs will reduce [police casualties](https://www.vox.com/2014/10/29/7083371/swat-no-knock-raids-police-killed-civilians-dangerous-work-drugs). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue is not drug legalization, but the functioning of the health insurances. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Taking drugs is not always a victimless crime, as drug users can harm others.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates with criminality, thievery, and risky sexual behavior. Responsibility is a state that is easily bypassed when you enter the flow of the drug world.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Producers and distributors are not able to control how consumers use their products. Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Fewer [productive](https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/outside-the-boardroom/article/Mass-incarceration-hurts-U-S-economy-7434722.php) people will be in jail. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Date-rape drugs are controlled presently. The current prohibition has not hindered the occurrence of date rape.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Such stress might be irrational, especially when it's related to unproblematic drug use. In that case, the psychological stress is the fault of the persons irrational beliefs."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Simply making all drugs legal would create a new big market niche exploited by resourceful pharmaceutical companies that could synthesize new, highly addictive substances everyday. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Strict quality controls will stimulate a fair competition amongst drug suppliers to offer the purest drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug users are detained along with violent criminals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug legalisation will make it easier to carry out [sexual assaults](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug-facilitated_sexual_assault).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This is an argument of the ends justifying the means. The government could generate more income by simply taking everyone's money by force - that doesn't make it a good choice. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would increase the probability of violence and offenses.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'High taxes may ensure that a black market for drugs remains with all the dangers it already has. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the government cannot take responsibility for a dangerous activity which takes place in society, there is no guarantee anyone else will.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalized, the prison system would be less over-crowded, which is a [significant issue](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2019.html) in the US.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It is unlikely that a low level drug dealer will shift to trafficking human beings the moment drugs get legalised. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalization of recreational drug use is not necessary for legalization of expanded drug research. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Young people could use fake IDs to buy drugs, the same way they currently do with alcohol and cigarettes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government would be giving up authority to empower the individual. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Selling harmful products is a poor long-term business strategy, as can be seen with tobacco companies. It only works as long as there is uncertainty in their harms. When the harms become apparent, people will take measures to stop using it as well as take measures to stop others from using it.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "There's no reasonable way for folks to measure whether or not a drug-induced hallucinatory episode will become a violent episode any more than there's a way to determine whether someone is an angry or violent drunk. Instead the police simply deal with the drunkards after the fact rather than taking away alcohol from everyone."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without proper education, people who are more prone to drug addiction may be more likely to get addicted to a drug.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are an experience that can build character.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [relatives](https://novarecoverycenter.com/drug-use/parental-drug-abuse/) of addicts are negatively impacted by their addiction. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Short-term pleasure from addictive drug consumption may lead to [irreversible impairments](https://www.health24.com/Medical/Osteoporosis/News/Graphic-This-drug-will-kill-you-within-two-years-20140709), damaging the consumer's quality of life."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't apply where there is no NHS or equivalent."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As this is also true under prohibition, it's an argument for proper education, not an argument against legalization. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Lots of drug addicts don't want to use drugs, but they can't just simply choose to stop using drugs, because they have an addiction."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Incarceration](https://beckleyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/paper_07.pdf) of drug offenders is expensive and a burden on taxpayers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal companies would be able to take over the drugs-related sector from illegal criminal organisations. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'While it might be better for society if a corporation created a less addictive drug, the actual incentive would be to create the most addictive drug imaginable. The corporation would then patent this to own a monopoly and charge a huge amount for continued use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs relate with [lower social skills](https://www.gatewayfoundation.org/substance-abuse-treatment-programs/effects-of-drug-abuse/) and antisocial behavior.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to the [Global Commission on Drug Policy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Commission_on_Drug_Policy), the war on drugs was a failure. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, as of 2018 there are roughly [235,000](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2018.html) inmates behind bars for drug-related crimes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since access to drugs is limited, and alcohol is widely available, this is to be expected and not proof of success.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The negative repercussions of drug use should be prosecuted on their own merit and context \\(without prosecuting the drug use itself\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is no way to determine in advance what the additional resources/revenue will be used for by the government. It may not be earmarked for harm reduction. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are still many other ways in which criminal associations could take advantage of the situation and legally start selling drugs or exploiting the farmers as they do now.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Non-violent dangers could increase, such as syringes being left in parks and other public spaces. This would create a risk of disease and injury to anyone in the area, especially children. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It also means there will be less demand for young people as workers in the black market. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Foreign countries' dealers might find it convenient to resupply in a nearby country where drugs have been legalized, thus boosting the phenomenon of international drug trafficking, expensive to track down and halt."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments would be able to check what cutting agents are used within the drugs, meaning they will be safer as potentially harmful cutting agents would be banned. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The evidence provided in this claim stems largely from importing cheaper cigarettes from the rest of Europe to the UK. The difference in quality is probably minimal. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without producing all drugs locally inside that border and banning imports, the situation would continue to support foreign criminal activity, including associated acts of violence and social destabilisation in other places where drugs are produced but not legal. {'type': 'con', 'text': "Without effective law enforcement, legalizing drugs might fuel criminal gang's economies \\(e.g., illegal trade\\). That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Regulated, corporate or government sale of these substances should not "target" low income areas and take advantage of disadvantaged people in the same way that current gangs, criminal organizations and other drug dealers currently do. {'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Incarceration](https://beckleyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/paper_07.pdf) of drug offenders is expensive and a burden on taxpayers.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The Federal Government \\(US\\) has no constitutional authority to regulate what citizens choose to put in their bodies. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having the option to buy regulated drugs is surely better than only having the black market option. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Cocaine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_harmfulness#/media/File:HarmCausedByDrugsTable.svg) is less harmful than alcohol, and only slightly more addictive. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
